Association</em>, 51: 3&ndash;34.</li>

<li>Raffa, M., 2016, <em>Claudio Tolemeo.</em> Armonica<em>. Con il
Commentario di Porfirio</em>, Milano: Bompiani.</li>

<li>Rashed, M., 2004, &ldquo;Priorit&eacute; de
l&rsquo;E&Iota;&Delta;&Omicron;&Sigma; ou du
&Gamma;&Epsilon;&Nu;&Omicron;&Sigma; entre Andronicos et Alexandre:
Vestiges Arabes et Grecs In&eacute;dits,&rdquo; <em>&Alpha;rabic
Sciences and Philosophy</em>, 14: 9&ndash;63.</li>

<li>Reydams-Schils, G., 2012, &ldquo;The Academy, the Stoics and
Cicero on Plato&rsquo;s Timaeus,&rdquo; in A.G. Long (ed.), <em>Plato
and the Stoics</em>, Cambridge: Cambridge University Press.</li>

<li>Ross, W.D., &amp; F.H. Fobes, 1929 [1967], <em>Theophrastus:
Metaphysics</em>, Oxford: Clarendon Press, 1929; reprinted,
Hildesheim: Georg Olms, 1967.</li>

<li>Sedley, D., 2021, &ldquo;Xenocrates&rsquo; Invention of
Platonism,&rdquo; in M. Erler, J.E. He&szlig;ler, F.M. Petrucci
(eds.), with the collaboration of M. McOsker, <em>Authority and
Authoritative Texts in the Platonist Tradition</em>, Cambridge:
Cambridge University Press, 12&ndash;37.</li>

<li>Thiel, D., 2006, <em>Die Philosophie des Xenokrates im Kontext der
Alten Akademie</em>, Munich-Leipzig: Saur Verlag.</li>

<li>Timotin, A., 2012, <em>La d&eacute;monologie platonicienne.
Histoire de la notion de daim&#333;n de Platon aux derniers
n&eacute;oplatoniciens</em>, Brill: Leiden-Boston.</li>

<li>Watts, Edward, 2007, &ldquo;Creating the Academy: Historical
Discourse and the Shape of Community in the Old Academy,&rdquo;
<em>The Journal of Hellenic Studies</em>, 127: 106&ndash;122.</li>
</ul>
</div> 

